Provides a version of Woddish's excellent Tiny Tank Fancy MBT and related things that have been sliced into major parts that are enabled to be quickly swapped and edited for customization by changing visibility of components between different options for turrets and weapons to make Predator based vehicles (Destructor, Annihilator, Baal, and Infernus) in both armoured and standard versions.

This is intended for designers and modelers to product their own faction customized vehicles from in a standardized and high quality form.

New part contributions are welcome!

was previously published as part of the MONOCEROS from Mars

If you like what I did and want to leave a tip it would be appreciated.
https://paypal.me/jimmyzimms

Edit 20220416: I've corrected some small mesh and alignment issues. I have additionally added a how to use guide for those new to Blender
Edit 20220526: Added flamer sponsons as weapon options.
Edit 20220603: Added turret armour and up-detailed the turret targeters
Edit 202250613: Added tank commander figures donated by Robbert Rysholt
Edit 20221014: Corrected some flipped normals on the flamestorm cannons- Thanks Adrian Brown! Default view set to have the extra armour panels visible
Edit 20230703: Small detail updates to the Baal turret. Added premade ready to print exports of the armoured predator upgrade models as a zip archive.
Edit 20230820: Added options to allow you to add chaos trim and icons to your Predator tanks. Chaos god icons from Bobbo01.
Edit 20230903: Thickened chaos trim based on feedback
Edit 20240616: Incorporated numerous sets of stowage options for turrets and chassis donated by the community to give additional variety to your tanks.
Edit 20240704: Added in Mk6 / 7 crew from Daffmakes
Edit 20240710: Added Chaos barrel tips for the las cannons

Provides a version of Woddish's excellent Tiny Tank Classic MBT and alman69uk's additional weapons that have been sliced into major parts that are enabled to be quickly swapped and edited for customization by changing visibility of components between different options for turrets and weapons to make Predator based vehicles (Destructor, Annihilator, Baal, Infernus, and plasma deimos pattern tanks). In addition, numerous mesh cleanup and extra details added.

This is intended for designers and modelers to product their own faction customized vehicles from in a standardized and high quality form. Comes with an easy How-To document explaining use for non-modelers as well.

If you like what I did and want to leave a tip it would be appreciated.
https://paypal.me/jimmyzimms

New part contributions are welcome!

Update 20230729: Added in flamer sponsons donated by SplayedPaintBrush

Update 20240518: Added new hedgehog option to tank and for those that love nothing more than rivets covering their tanks, you no longer have to wait!

Update 20240627: Incorporated DaffMakes most excellent crew models into the builder. Now you can select if you want an open or closed hatch (former for the crew) and can chose from 6 different poses in Mk2-Mk6 armour on your exported turret! Give you many new options for your customized armies.

Tiny tanks! The perfect thing to give a sense of scale to your tiny titans, tiny aircraft, or tiny anything! Add them as base decoration, add them as terrain decoration, create tiny war dioramas, do whatever you want with them! Anything is made better with the addition of tiny tanks.
Do you like going faster than all of your tiny brethren? Do you like shooting more tiny bullets than them as well? Then this is the tiny tank for you! Souped up tiny engines! Tiny gatling guns AND tiny machine guns to make sure more tiny bullets are spent every time you pull the tiny trigger! What more could a tiny soldier want?
Tiny tanks are intended for resin printers.

This model is a Proxy for the MK1 Mars Pattern Predator (AKA Rogue Trader Style).

Based on my Epic MK1 Mars Pattern Rhino Proxy
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2823744

The "FULL" model is for display purposes only. It will likely be ugly as sin if you try to print it.

Print at 100% for regular 6mm Epic scale
Print at 105% for "Truescale" 6mm
Print at 110% for 8mm New AT 2018 Scale

CHANGELOG
2018-03-15 - Added a Post for Turret alignment. Flagging as Complete.
2018-03-13 - After a successful overnight print run, I discovered a couple of holes in the Mesh and more misalignments due to workflow issues. Updated Files have been uploaded.
2018-03-12 - I have not printed, therefore have not tuned this model. I do not expect any issues with the portions shared with the Rhino.
NOTE: If you downloaded this thing prior to 9PM EST I have found a bug in the model caused by me running it through MS 3D Builder. This bug caused a few mis-alignments between the parts that make up the various meshes. Please accept my apologies I will be posting new files Shortly.

This is based on my first project in Fusion 360 and was started in SketchUp 2018. Enjoy!
